A Message from Hardinge Inc.







Company Profile

Hardinge is a global designer, manufacturer and distributor of machine tools, specializing in SUPER PRECISION™ and precision CNC Lathes, Milling Machines, high-end cylindrical and jig Grinding Machines, and technologically advanced Workholding  & Rotary Products.



                        





Hardinge Inc.














As Seen In Modern Machine Shop






 
 Catch Up on PMTS 2017’s Live Demonstrations with This Video Playlist
            
                Covering workholding, Swiss-type turning, multitasking machines and more, the seven talks in the YouTube playlist are a good recap of the latest in production machining technology.





 
 ID, OD, Face, Taper, Radius, Contour Grinding in Single Chucking
            
                Eastec 2017: Hardinge Grinding Group, a subsidiary of Hardinge Inc., will showcase its USACH 100‐T4 machine for ID/OD precision cylindrical grinding in a variety of industries. 





 
 Hardinge Group to Host Machine Technology Show 
            
                The June 6-8 event will feature products, seminars, networking and more. 








 
 Turning Center Achieves 5-Micron Tolerances
            
                PMTS 2017: The Hardinge Conquest H51 lathe is capable of turn tolerances down to traditional grinding levels of 5 microns, according to the company.





 
 Five-Axis VMC Offers Power and Precision
            
                Hardinge offers its next-generation Bridgeport XT 630 five-axis VMC designed to achieve maximum capacity and performance in the aerospace, die/mold, medical and automotive industries. 





 
 Turning Center Series Features Collet-Ready Spindle
            
                Hardinge’s Talent series of CNC turning centers, including the 42 and 51 models, is designed for accuracy, flexibility and durability in a compact machine.







 
 Compact VMCs Benefit Job Shops, OEMs
            
                The Bridgeport V480 and V710 vertical machining centers from Hardinge are suitable for applications ranging from job shop work to high-production manufacturing with fast rapid traverse rates, high axis and spindle acceleration/deceleration, and a powerful control.





 
 Hydraulic Actuating Cylinder Features Built-In Trapping
            
                Forkardt Inc., part of the Hardinge Group, has released its HWC hydraulic actuating cylinder offering higher rpm and operating pressures. 





 
 Steady Rest Supports Long Workpieces without Deflection
            
                Hardinge’s hydraulically-operated Forkardt SRFN1 compact steady rest is a new attachment designed for the company’s Conquest H51 CNC turning center. 







 
 Line of Accessories Expands Collet System
            
                Hardinge will display a new line of accessories for the quick-change FlexC collet systems, which provide fast changeover, high accuracy and a wide gripping range for stock variation. 





 
 Fully Digital Five-Axis VMC
            
                Hardinge will display the new Bridgeport XT 630 VMC, a five-axis machining center that is fully-digital and is designed for use in the aerospace, die/mold, medical and automotive industries. 





 
 CNC Turning Center Features Quick-Change Spindle
            
                The Hardinge Talent 51 MSY CNC turning center features the company’s quick-change collet-ready spindle designed for improved part accuracy and surface finish capabilities compared to conventional spindles. 







 
 Cylindrical Grinder Improves Part Surface Quality
            
                Hardinge’s Kellenberger Varia universal cylindrical grinding machine is designed for improved part surface quality and functional design with high-precision technology.





 
 AMT Elects Officers, Board of Directors for 2016-2017
            
                Among the new leaders of the board are executives from Hardinge, Mazak and AME.





 
 VMC’s Improved Automatic Pallet Changer Handles Heavier Loads
            
                Hardinge offers Bridgeport’s fully digital Conquest V480 APC E series vertical machining center with Mitsubishi M70 CNC. 







 
 Hardinge Hires West Coast Regional Sales Manager, Turning and Milling
            
                Meghan Tranchina’s territory will include a number of western U.S. states as well as part of Canada.





 
 Aztalan Aims  for Rapid Adjustment
            
                Aztalan Engineering shortened its lead times by switching to a short-run cell model for its prototype jobs and implementing a company-wide QRM strategy.





 
 Hardinge Hires Southeast Sales Manager
            
                Kennedy Pope will represent the Turning and Milling Group.  







 
 Bar and Chucking Machine Offers High Accuracy, Part Finish
            
                Hardinge Inc. offers its Conquest H51 bar and chucking machine featuring the company’s quick-change Collet-Ready spindle.





 
 Hardinge Hires Turning/Milling Machine Group Director
            
                A new sales and service director will focus on the North American turning and milling market. 
























